description:
&lt;p&gt;Reporting directly to the Director of Strategy, People and Partnerships this new position of Director of IT and Analytics will serve as a strategic partner and a member of the senior management team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for helping the company move forward with advances in technology and methods of processing and managing information, serving as a leader and innovator for the company&#39;s Information Technology and Business Analytics Departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will oversee DHU&#39;s technology-related strategies, initiatives and plans for the company&#39;s technology needs addressing any tech-related problems, analyse information and communicate with other Directors to make sure there is consistency throughout the organisation in their approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will play a key role in maintaining ISO accreditations, facilitating IT systems development and associated control assurance plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role’s remit is to drive innovation and change by providing technology solutions to support business challenges and improve the way care is delivered to patients. The post holder will ensure process and technology are aligned to our staff to deliver time critical contract services across the East Midlands region. In addition, the post will also be responsible for innovating the service model for NHS 111/Integrated Urgent Care as part of the complete digitalisation across DHU Health Care CIC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director is a key contributor to DHU’s strategy and planning process being responsible both for IT operations, Business Analytics, and for technology and digital innovation. It is critical to build strong and productive relationships both internally and externally with the NHS Commissioners and Trust Providers, including with DHU’s formal partnerships and joint ventures, and acting as a true system partner and making IT a business enabler. They will represent DHU on Contract Management Boards with our NHS Commissioners, as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will support the ongoing development of the business model by identifying potential new services, markets and customers, with a clear framework for growth to enable the business to remain a sustainable operation. The post holder will work on key strategic programmes of work and be comfortable leading cross-departmental and multi-disciplinary delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate&lt;/span&gt; will support DHU’s strategic business development work to grow the business in line with organisational strategy. Through engaging and influencing key stakeholders at all levels within the NHS this will aim to facilitate potential business opportunities or contract extensions. Furthermore they will play a role in representing DHU in contract negotiations and tendering procurement exercises.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support the Director of Strategy, People and Partnerships to drive innovation and insight to ensure DHU Health Care CIC is “leading-edge” in patient care and responsiveness of healthcare services regionally and nationwide, and to ensure the successful delivery of multiple revenue-generating service lines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must be able to provide business leaders with strategic and tactical insight and be viewed by them as a value-added business partner, producing Management Information (MI) for the Executive Board, making sure records can be shared, while mindful of regulations like GDPR or ISO.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also be nominated as the Senior Information Risk Owner (SIRO) for DHU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, candidates will be excellent communicators, with the ability to create impact, by engaging and influencing key stakeholders in order to facilitate positive change. They must be driven and passionate about creating and shaping an innovative strategic vision for the best possible long term benefit of the organisation and our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an initial discussion about this opportunity please contact Stephen Bateman (Chief Executive Officer) on 0300 1000 422 or if you are ready to apply please contact our retained recruitment consultant Nikki Kinsey at nikki.kinsey@sellickpartnership.co.uk to obtain a recruitment pack.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
